regexp explanation:&lt;br&gt;

 - \p{L} – to allow all letters from any language
 - \p{N} – for numbers
 - \p{P} – for punctuation
 - \p{Z} – for whitespace separators
 - ^ is for negation, so all these expressions will be whitelisted

